* Added an optional Redis-backed cache for the host-by-node_key lookup on the osquery authentication path, gated by `FLEET_REDIS_HOST_CACHE_ENABLED` (default off). When enabled, successful lookups are cached for `FLEET_REDIS_HOST_CACHE_TTL` (default 60s, ±10% jitter) and invalidated on writes that mutate cached host fields. Reduces reader-side DB load at scale without changing the HTTP contract.
